                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>100 feet.</p>\n<p>The thunderbird is surrounded by a cyclone of wind and driving rain. This area is greater difficult terrain for flying creatures, who must successfully @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Maneuver in Flight]{Maneuver in Flight} (DC 27) or be blown 30 feet away from the thunderbird. Creatures on the ground must succeed at a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"27\" data-pf2-traits=\"air,aura,evocation,primal,water,move,concentrate\" data-pf2-label=\"Storm Aura DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Reflex</span> save to perform any move action and are knocked @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Prone]{Prone} on a critical failure.</p>\n<p>The driving rain in the storm aura imposes a -2 circumstance penalty on Perception checks and extinguishes smaller flames.</p>\n<p>A thunderbird can deactivate or activate the storm aura as a free action with the concentrate trait.</p>"
